- 可以走路吗?- 为何不呢

493
00:34:35,117 --> 00:34:36,869
Beautiful city.
漂亮的城市

494
00:34:37,077 --> 00:34:39,246
The Romans call it"The Land of the Sirens..."
罗马人叫它"妖妇之城"

495
00:34:39,454 --> 00:34:40,914
from Homer's Odyssey.
出自荷马的《奥德赛》

496
00:34:41,206 --> 00:34:42,958
Is that so? Aren't you clever?
真的吗?你真聪明

497
00:34:44,501 --> 00:34:47,671
- I read it somewhere.- I like a good read myself.
- 我在哪里读到的- 我也喜欢阅读

498
00:34:47,921 --> 00:34:49,798
Nothing too laborious. I don't wantto tamper with natural ignorance.
别太累，我不想影响自然的无知

499
00:34:49,965 --> 00:34:51,967
- It's the key to happiness.- Do you really think so?
- 是快乐的钥匙- 你真那么想吗?

500
00:34:52,176 --> 00:34:54,136
Absolutely. Good health,it's important, but...
绝对是，健康，很重要...

501
00:34:54,678 --> 00:34:57,681
ignorance is the key. Too muchknowledge and you're doomed.
无知是钥匙，太多知识你就被限制住了

502
00:35:08,775 --> 00:35:10,444
Well, here we are.
嗯，到了

503
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:13,155
Aren't you going to invite mein for a nightcap?
你都不邀请我进睡前酒吗?

504
00:35:15,949 --> 00:35:18,702
The sirens were said to behalf woman, half monster.
传说中的妖妇是半人半魔

505
00:35:20,037 --> 00:35:22,164
They lured the sailors withtheir songs.
她们用歌声引诱水手

506
00:35:23,832 --> 00:35:26,960
The ships crashed on therocks and the men all drowned.
船只触礁，水手溺水

507
00:35:28,086 --> 00:35:30,964
Oh, let's go in. You can tell memore about it.
哦，进去吧，你再多告诉我一些

508
00:35:42,100 --> 00:35:44,895
Poor Lady Plymdale, I think shereally likes Tuppy.
可怜的Plymdale女士,我觉得她是真喜欢Tuppy

509
00:35:46,104 --> 00:35:48,065
- Where do you suppose they went?- Who?
- 你觉得他们去哪里了?- 谁?

510
00:35:49,107 --> 00:35:50,359
Tuppy and Mrs Erlynne.
Tuppy 和Erlynne太太

